Meet <b>Kyle</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Kyle lives at <a href='/home/?user=kkyyllee932'>6686 Port Avenue</a> in Lakeview, and is one of Millsberry's sports stars. Since April 20, 2005, he has wowed his schoolmates and classmates with his stellar athletic ability.<br><br>Kyle has always been active, and sports are such a part of his life that sometimes he'll be thinking about football strategy and corner kicks without even realizing it! Hockey is another of his favorite sports, and he is constantly working on his defensive skill and slapshot. You can often find him in Peabody Park [link] kicking a ball around with friends or working on his spiral.<br><br>When he's not flexing his athletic muscle, Kyle loves listening to music. Oldies, modern rock, and heavy metal all have a home on his stereo system. He likes classic tunes as well as pretty out-there stuff! But that's the way Kyle is???open to new things, and diverse in his tastes. He's the same way with food. He enjoys varying the dishes he eats, and will always try something once.<br><br>Kyle's home is where he relaxes after practice and does his morning routine of stretches and sit-ups. Stop by Lakeview and check out his style. His favorite colors are gold, green, and silver, so if you want to get him a gift, try one of those colors. <br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Kyle, and congratulations on being named Citizen of the Week!<br></div>
